HEADWORD: Modalist
<hw>Mo"dal*ist</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Theol.)</fld> <def>One who
regards Father, Son, and Spirit as modes of being, and not as persons,
thus denying personal distinction in the Trinity.</def>
<rj><au>Eadie.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

